The paper discusses the translation of threaded code into event-driven code, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the implementation of these translations in a language extension for writing concurrent systems (cs.SE) and the performance of the resulting code (cs.SY, cs.LG).
